what:
where:
Gulf Connexions
-
Dubai
The role will take charge or a portfolio of large GCC or UAE Corporations and will be reporting directly to the Managing Director of Investment Banking Coverage. The successful candidate should have the ability to strengthen existing and develop new corporate relations across various sectors of the market, throughout the UAE and GCC.
Responsibilities:
Overlook a client coverage that includes large corporates across the Gulf and quasi sovereign state entities/Sovereign Wealth Funds. Identify new trends/developments in the field of specialty and advice clients, on a more focused data gathering. Deliver specific Investment Banking products and services to clients.
Requirements:
A minimum of 6 years of experience, at least 4 of which have been in the region with a top regional or international bank/ organization. Knowledge of complex Corporate and Investment products is mandatory. High level of academics and International experience. International banking background.
Candidates who qualify for this position may kindly quote the Job Title in the subject of your respective email and send your CV as an attachment in MS Word Document format to benedict.santos@gulfconnexions.com or contact +973 17 565 366 Only short listed candidates will be contacted.
